  "system": {
    "description": {
      "gm": "",
      "value": "<p>You generate a strong localized quake over an area, trying to throw your enemies off their feet. Creatures within the area on the ground need to make a Reflex saving throw; on a failure, a creature takes 2d6 bludgeoning damage and is knocked prone. Casting this spell with 3 actions causes the localized area to become difficult terrain for 1 minute, as the aftershock lingers in the area to impede creatures trying to walk over the terrain.</p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Success </strong>The creature takes half damage, but is not knocked prone.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure </strong>The creature takes full damage and is knocked prone.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> The creature takes double damage, is knocked prone.   </p>\n<p>    </p>\n<p><strong>Heightened(4th) </strong>The damage increases to 4d6; on a critical failure, the creature is stunned 1.</p>\n<p><strong>Heightened(8th) </strong>The damage increases to 8d6; on a failure, the creature is also stunned 1 and on a critical failure, the creature is stunned 2.</p>"
    },
